1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,400
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:06,480
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:11,360
My name is Catherine and today we've got a very special lesson for you all about time.
我是Catherine，今天我们为大家准备了一节非常特别的课程，全部关于时间。

4
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:12,360
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:17,280
We're going to concentrate a little bit on some specific points of grammar this time
这次我们会重点讲一些具体的语法点。

6
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:21,280
and we're going to talk about the morning routine, what you do in the mornings.
我们会讨论早晨的例行事务，也就是你早上做的事情。

7
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:24,280
Well, let's take a look first at the word routine.
好，我们先来看看“routine”这个词。

8
00:00:24,280 --> 00:00:28,440
This is our vocabulary preview for today.
这是今天的词汇预览。

9
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:30,240
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

10
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:32,960
Alright so a routine or the morning routine.
好的，所以“routine”或“morning routine”。

11
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:34,240
What is a routine?
什么是“routine”？

12
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:41,080
A routine is basically your habit for a certain period of time.
“routine”基本上就是你在某段时间内的习惯。

13
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:46,640
So for example, your routine in the morning is what you do when you wake up.
比如，你早上的例行事务就是你醒来后做的事情。

14
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:48,160
Get breakfast and go to work.
吃早餐然后去上班。

15
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:51,120
You can also have an evening routine.
你也可以有晚上的例行事务。

16
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:54,520
It's what you always do before you go to bed.
就是你睡觉前总是做的事情。

17
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,520
Exactly.
没错。

18
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:59,760
Everyone has a routine, what they do in the mornings, maybe what you do at night before
每个人都有例行事务，他们早上做什么，也许你晚上睡觉前做什么。

19
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:00,960
going to bed.
睡觉前。

20
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:03,360
So that's what we're going to talk about today.
这就是我们今天要讨论的内容。

21
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:04,360
That's right.
没错。

22
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:05,360
You can also have an exercise routine.
你也可以有锻炼的例行事务。

23
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,880
So basically anything with steps.
所以基本上任何有步骤的事情。

24
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:10,600
One, two, three, four, five, that you always do the same way.
一、二、三、四、五，你总是以同样的方式做。

25
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:11,600
That's a routine.
那就是例行事务。

26
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:12,600
Exactly.
没错。

27
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:13,600
Right.
对。

28
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:14,600
So that's what we're going to take a look at today.
所以这就是我们今天要看的。

29
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:26,080
Let's actually jump right into our dialogue and listen to Stephanie's routine.
让我们直接进入对话，听听Stephanie的例行事务。

30
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:28,240
Stephanie did you just get to school?
Stephanie，你刚到学校吗？

31
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:31,040
But you were up and about when I left the dorm this morning.
但我早上离开宿舍的时候你已经起床活动了。

32
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,760
That was about an hour and a half ago.
那大约是一个半小时前。

33
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:33,760
This happens all the time.
这种事经常发生。

34
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:36,760
Why do you always take so long to get ready in the mornings?
为什么你早上总是花那么长时间准备？

35
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:37,880
It's a skill.
这是一种技能。

36
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:39,560
What can I say?
我能说什么呢？

37
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,640
I don't know why.
我不知道为什么。

38
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,600
I just have a long routine.
我只是有一个很长的例行事务。

39
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:45,080
Please explain because it makes no sense to me.
请解释一下，因为我觉得这完全说不通。

40
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:47,760
How can a girl's routine be so complicated?
一个女生的例行事务怎么能这么复杂？

41
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:53,120
You get up, you shower, you get dressed, you brush your teeth, you're out the door.
你起床、洗澡、穿衣服、刷牙，然后出门。

42
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,720
Half an hour tops.
最多半小时。

43
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:59,640
Jacob, you have the luxury of having a haircut that rarely needs styling.
Jacob，你幸运地有一个几乎不需要造型的发型。

44
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,760
I don't.
我没有。

45
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:05,080
I have to set aside about an hour and a half to get ready in the mornings.
我早上必须留出大约一个半小时来准备。

46
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:08,140
Every day I wake up and head straight for the shower.
每天我醒来就直接去洗澡。

47
00:02:08,140 --> 00:02:10,040
Every second day I wash my hair.
我每隔一天洗一次头发。

48
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:15,720
If it's a hair washing day, I frequently need to wash my hair twice because it gets really
如果是洗头日，我经常需要洗两次头发，因为它会变得很油。

49
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:16,720
oily.
很油。

50
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:20,360
Then, I usually put in a conditioner and have to rinse that out too.
然后，我通常会涂护发素，还得把它冲洗掉。

51
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:26,000
Because my hair is so long, I seldom manage to take a shower in under 20 minutes.
因为我的头发很长，我很少能在20分钟内洗完澡。

52
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:30,800
Afterwards, I often put on a pot of coffee and get dressed while I wait for it to brew.
之后，我经常煮一壶咖啡，在等它煮好的时候穿衣服。

53
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,800
I take a long time to get dressed in the morning.
我早上穿衣服要花很长时间。

54
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:37,640
Every now and then I remember to choose my outfit the night before, but usually I do
偶尔我会记得前一天晚上选好衣服，但通常我都是早上才选。

55
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:39,300
it in the morning.
早上才选。

56
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:43,520
In all, getting dressed takes about half an hour, at which time my hair is now semi-dry
总的来说，穿衣服大约需要半小时，这时我的头发半干了。

57
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,920
so then I have to style my hair.
所以然后我得打理头发。

58
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:50,800
From time to time I'll put my hair up, but oftentimes I blow dry it straight.
有时候我会把头发扎起来，但通常我会用吹风机吹直。

59
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:55,360
And then, because of the texture of my hair, I regularly have to flat iron it to keep it
然后，因为我的发质，我经常需要用直发夹板来防止它毛躁。

60
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,000
from frizzing.
防止它毛躁。

61
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,240
That's another 20 minutes or so.
那又是大约20分钟。

62
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,400
After that, I have my daily makeup routine.
之后，我进行每天的化妆流程。

63
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:06,000
True, I hardly ever see you without your hair done and your makeup on, even when you show
确实，我几乎从没见过你不弄头发、不化妆的样子，即使你穿着运动裤来上课。

64
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
up to class in sweatpants.
穿着运动裤来上课。

65
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,480
Tell me, how long does it take you to choose that outfit in the morning?
告诉我，你早上选那套衣服要花多长时间？

66
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,480
Not funny.
不好笑。

67
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:19,040
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

68
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:21,360
So obviously she has a very complicated routine.
所以很明显她有一个非常复杂的例行事务。

69
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,920
I don't know if all girls are like this.
我不知道是不是所有女生都这样。

70
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:27,000
I'm not like this, but I think a lot of girls, and some guys are.
我不是这样，但我认为很多女生，还有一些男生是这样。

71
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,160
I don't want to be sexist here.
我不想在这里有性别歧视。

72
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:33,680
I know some guys who take their time in the morning and are very, very particular about
我知道有些男生早上会慢慢来，而且非常非常在意自己的外表。

73
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,680
the way that they look.
自己的外表。

74
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:35,680
Really?
真的吗？

75
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,680
Wow.
哇。

76
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:39,800
So, obviously everyone has their morning routine in different ways.
所以，显然每个人都有自己不同的早晨例行事务。

77
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:42,120
And it was interesting to see how she described it.
看她怎么描述这件事很有趣。

78
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:47,440
So why don't we take a look at Language Takeaway.
所以我们来看看“语言要点”部分。

79
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:49,640
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

80
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:54,240
So today's Language Takeaway, like I said at the beginning of the podcast, is all about
所以今天的语言要点，就像我在播客开头说的，全是关于

81
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,240
time.
时间。

82
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,760
So we're going to look at some of these important time adverbs.
所以我们要看一些重要的时间副词。

83
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,760
That's right.
没错。

84
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,280
These are called adverbs of frequency.
这些被称为频率副词。

85
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:04,040
And basically, they are telling us how we do things.
基本上，它们告诉我们做事情的方式。

86
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:07,800
If we do something all the time or if we never do something.
如果我们一直做某事，或者从不做某事。

87
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,080
Or everything in between.
或者介于两者之间的一切。

88
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,080
Exactly.
正是。

89
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:14,600
So the first couple we have today are very, very common words.
所以今天的前几个词是非常非常常见的词。

90
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:15,760
You're going to hear these a lot.
你会经常听到它们。

91
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,280
The first one is frequently.
第一个是“frequently”。

92
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,680
Okay, frequently.
好的，“frequently”。

93
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:24,320
So, if you do something frequently, consider it to be about 75% of the time.
所以，如果你经常做某事，可以认为大约75%的时间。

94
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:27,040
Maybe a little bit more, almost 85% of the time.
可能多一点，几乎85%的时间。

95
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,040
Right.
对。

96
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:30,680
So it's not always, but it's very often.
所以不是总是，但非常频繁。

97
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:35,560
So for example, so I frequently forget to take my keys when I'm leaving the house, which
例如，我经常在离开家时忘记带钥匙，这

98
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,800
is a very big problem.
是个大问题。

99
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,800
Exactly.
正是。

100
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:41,520
So considering out of seven days, maybe you forget your keys five days.
所以考虑到七天里，你可能五天忘记钥匙。

101
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,520
Not so good.
不太好。

102
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,520
All right.
好的。

103
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,520
So that's frequently.
这就是“frequently”。

104
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:48,120
Now let's move on to another one that's actually a lot less.
现在来看另一个频率低得多的词。

105
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,720
We talk about seldom.
我们谈谈“seldom”。

106
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:53,960
Well, Marco has told me that he seldom forgets his keys.
嗯，Marco告诉我他很少忘记钥匙。

107
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:56,960
That means he almost always remembers them.
这意味着他几乎总是记得。

108
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:57,960
Right.
对。

109
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,600
So seldom is a negative adverb.
所以“seldom”是一个否定副词。

110
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,680
It's saying that almost never.
它表示几乎从不。

111
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,680
Okay.
好的。

112
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:07,080
So if I say, for example, I seldom go to the movies.
所以如果我说，例如，我很少去看电影。

113
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,080
That's too bad.
那太可惜了。

114
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:09,080
I like the movies.
我喜欢电影。

115
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,080
Right.
对。

116
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:13,640
Well, that means that I maybe go to the movie theater once a month.
嗯，那意味着我可能一个月去一次电影院。

117
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:14,640
Yeah.
是的。

118
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:15,640
Not very often.
不经常。

119
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:16,640
Seldom.
很少。

120
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:17,640
Not very often.
不经常。

121
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,640
Seldom.
很少。

122
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:19,640
All right.
好的。

123
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:22,480
Now going back to a positive adverb of frequency, we have often.
现在回到一个肯定的频率副词，我们有“often”。

124
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:25,520
You described frequently as very often.
你把“frequently”描述为非常频繁。

125
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,520
That's right.
没错。

126
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:33,320
You can also say, I often forget my keys or it often rains in tropical places.
你也可以说，我经常忘记钥匙，或者热带地区经常下雨。

127
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:35,360
This means this is a common thing.
这意味着这是常见的事情。

128
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,360
Exactly.
正是。

129
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:40,680
So again, let's consider it to be about 70 to 80% of the time.
所以再次，我们把它看作大约70%到80%的时间。

130
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:45,000
Now with pronunciation, some people like to pronounce often, right?
关于发音，有些人喜欢读成“often”，对吧？

131
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,560
They kind of leave out the strong T sound.
他们有点省略了强T音。

132
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,620
Well, other people say often.
嗯，其他人说“often”。

133
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,620
That's right.
没错。

134
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:52,620
Both forms are correct, right?
两种形式都正确，对吧？

135
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:53,620
Yes, they're both correct.
是的，它们都正确。

136
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:56,640
So you're safe using either of these.
所以用任何一种都没问题。

137
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,640
Right.
对。

138
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:58,640
Okay.
好的。

139
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:01,600
And our third adverb of frequency, no, our fourth.
我们的第三个频率副词，不，是第四个。

140
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:07,720
And our fourth adverb of frequency is also a positive one and we say usually.
我们的第四个频率副词也是一个肯定的，我们说“usually”。

141
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:12,360
Usually means this is something that you do pretty consistently.
“Usually”意味着你相当一致地做某事。

142
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:16,840
I usually brush my hair before I go to sleep.
我通常在睡觉前梳头。

143
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:19,520
That means not always, but almost every day.
这意味着不是总是，但几乎每天。

144
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,520
Right.
对。

145
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:22,800
So let's consider out of seven days, you do it six times.
所以考虑七天里，你做六次。

146
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,800
Yeah.
是的。

147
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,800
I usually do this.
我通常这样做。

148
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:25,800
Okay.
好的。

149
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:28,920
So usually is again, very, very common.
所以“usually”再次非常非常常见。

150
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:35,480
And something in between maybe 60% of the time, 50% of the time we say regularly.
而介于中间，大约60%的时间，50%的时间，我们说“regularly”。

151
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:40,640
Well, I think of the word regularly as being very closely related to regular.
嗯，我认为“regularly”这个词与“regular”密切相关。

152
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:45,840
So basically if I have a schedule, I do the same thing every day.
所以基本上，如果我有日程安排，我每天做同样的事。

153
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,580
I do it regularly.
我定期做。

154
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:49,480
But sometimes there's a special occasion.
但有时有特殊情况。

155
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:54,720
For example, I regularly run five kilometers after work when I go to the gym.
例如，我下班后去健身房时，通常跑五公里。

156
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:57,440
But sometimes when I want to go out with my friends, I don't run.
但有时我想和朋友出去，就不跑了。

157
00:06:57,440 --> 00:07:00,160
So it's not always, but it is pretty regular.
所以不是总是，但相当规律。

158
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,160
Exactly.
正是。

159
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:06,880
So regularly means you do it very often, but there are some exceptions.
所以“regularly”意味着你经常做，但有一些例外。

160
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:07,880
Okay.
好的。

161
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:12,760
Now those are adverbs of frequency, but we have a couple of other phrases that are very
这些是频率副词，但我们还有几个其他短语也非常

162
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:15,900
similar so we want to take a look at those as well.
类似，所以我们也要看看它们。

163
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:20,840
Let's go back to the beginning of Stephanie's routine when she said that every day I wake
让我们回到斯蒂芬妮日常生活的开头，她说每天我醒

164
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:21,840
up.
来。

165
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:22,840
Okay.
好的。

166
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:26,440
So every day means 100% of the time every single day.
所以“每天”意味着100%的时间，每一天。

167
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,920
Monday to Sunday.
从周一到周日。

168
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:28,920
Exactly.
没错。

169
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:31,140
So obviously you wake up every day.
所以显然你每天都会醒来。

170
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:34,200
Or I brush my teeth twice every day.
或者我每天刷两次牙。

171
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:36,920
So that's 100% of the time.
所以那是100%的时间。

172
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:41,360
Now if we say every second day, what does that mean?
现在如果我们说“每隔一天”，那是什么意思？

173
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:47,660
That means Monday yes, Tuesday no, Wednesday yes, Thursday no, or any day.
那意味着周一洗，周二不洗，周三洗，周四不洗，或者任何一天。

174
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:51,520
So basically she says I wash my hair every second day.
所以基本上她说我每隔一天洗一次头发。

175
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:55,960
That means one day I wash my hair, but the next day I don't.
这意味着有一天我洗头发，但第二天我不洗。

176
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:59,600
The day after that though, I wash it again.
不过再下一天，我又洗了。

177
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:00,600
Every second day.
每隔一天。

178
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,600
Okay.
好的。

179
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:06,160
So you can say every second day and I think you can also say every other day.
所以你可以说“每隔一天”，我想你也可以说“每两天一次”。

180
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,160
Every other day.
每两天一次。

181
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,160
So every other day or every second day.
所以是每隔一天或者每两天一次。

182
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:11,560
He calls his mother every other day.
他每隔一天给他妈妈打电话。

183
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,560
Very good.
非常好。

184
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,560
Alright.
好的。

185
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:18,600
And she also said that every now and then I remember to choose my outfit.
她还说，我偶尔会记得挑选我的衣服。

186
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,600
Okay.
好的。

187
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:20,600
Well, this one's interesting.
嗯，这个挺有意思的。

188
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,080
This is not very frequent.
这个频率不高。

189
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:25,000
This is basically saying sometimes.
这基本上就是说“有时候”。

190
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,300
Sometimes.
有时候。

191
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:27,560
So now and then.
所以是“偶尔”。

192
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:31,920
Every now and then means I sometimes do it, I sometimes don't do it.
“偶尔”的意思是，我有时候做，有时候不做。

193
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:36,400
Every now and then I really want to eat chocolate so I buy a candy bar.
我偶尔特别想吃巧克力，就会买一块巧克力棒。

194
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:37,400
Okay.
好的。

195
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:40,520
So basically you want to eat chocolate twice in a month.
所以基本上你一个月想吃两次巧克力。

196
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,680
Yeah, not very often.
对，不经常。

197
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:42,680
Not very often.
不经常。

198
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:43,680
Okay.
好的。

199
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:47,600
And another one that's very similar is from time to time.
还有一个很相似的表达是“时不时地”。

200
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,720
So Marco said that he doesn't go to the movies very frequently.
所以马可说他不经常去看电影。

201
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,520
So he goes from time to time.
所以他时不时会去。

202
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,520
Right.
对。

203
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:58,120
So I can say I seldom go to the movies or I can say I like to go to the movies from
所以我可以说我很少去看电影，或者可以说我喜欢时不时去

204
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,480
time to time.
看电影。

205
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,560
That's right.
没错。

206
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,240
Or this girl is describing her appearance.
或者这个女孩在描述她的外表。

207
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:04,760
She says from time to time I put my hair up.
她说我时不时会把头发盘起来。

208
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,520
So that means most of the time.
这意味着大多数时候。

209
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,520
That means sometimes it's down.
意思是有时候是披着的。

210
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:09,520
Sometimes it's up.
有时候是盘起来的。

211
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,520
Right.
对。

212
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:14,960
So as you can see there are many different ways of describing the frequency or how many
所以你看，有很多不同的方式可以描述频率，或者你

213
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:18,880
times you do certain actions or your routine.
做某些动作或日常事务的次数。

214
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:22,200
So you can use this with a lot of things when you're describing.
所以你在描述时可以用在很多事情上。

215
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:26,480
And we encourage you to try some of these new ones because a lot of English learners
我们鼓励你尝试一些新的表达，因为很多英语学习者

216
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:29,840
use the same time adverbs whenever they speak.
说话时总是用同样的时间副词。

217
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:33,520
So try and really use some of these and challenge yourself.
所以试着真正用上这些，挑战一下自己。

218
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,520
Exactly.
正是。

219
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:37,360
All right so that's all we have for language takeaway.
好了，这就是我们语言点学习的全部内容。

220
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:41,920
Why don't we move on now to Fluency Builder.
我们接下来进入流利度训练吧。

221
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:44,280
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

222
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:53,280
Okay so using some of these adverbs I could say I can say I regularly make a pot of coffee
好的，所以用这些副词，我可以说，我可以说我早上经常煮一壶咖啡。

223
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,280
in the morning.
在早上。

224
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:55,280
Okay.
好的。

225
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,480
So a pot of coffee.
所以是一壶咖啡。

226
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,120
You regularly make a pot of coffee.
你经常煮一壶咖啡。

227
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:00,080
That means you like to drink coffee every day.
这意味着你每天喜欢喝咖啡。

228
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,080
That's right.
没错。

229
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,560
I always need my cup of coffee in the morning.
我早上总是需要一杯咖啡。

230
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,440
So I usually make it first thing.
所以我通常第一件事就是煮咖啡。

231
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,120
So a pot of coffee.
所以是一壶咖啡。

232
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,320
We know what a cup of coffee is.
我们知道一杯咖啡是什么。

233
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,320
But a pot of coffee.
但一壶咖啡。

234
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,320
What is a pot?
壶是什么？

235
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:17,560
A pot is basically the container that you use when you brew coffee when you make it.
壶基本上是你煮咖啡时用的容器。

236
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:22,200
So you put the coffee beans in the machine and instead of having a cup underneath you
所以你把咖啡豆放进机器里，而不是在下面放一个杯子，

237
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,640
have a bigger container that's a pot.
你放一个更大的容器，那就是壶。

238
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:27,720
You can also have a pot of tea.
你也可以有一壶茶。

239
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,720
Exactly.
没错。

240
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,720
It's many cups.
它相当于很多杯。

241
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,120
Usually eight or ten cups.
通常八到十杯。

242
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,120
All right.
好的。

243
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,120
So what is that verb?
那那个动词是什么？

244
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,120
To brew coffee.
泡咖啡。

245
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:38,480
I think it's a very nice kind of fancy way of saying making coffee.
我觉得这是一种很优雅的说法，相当于“做咖啡”。

246
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:39,480
Brew a pot of coffee.
煮一壶咖啡。

247
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,120
I'm brewing some coffee.
我正在煮咖啡。

248
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,120
All right.
好的。

249
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:47,840
So apart from coffee and all of these things, let's take a look at some of the specific
除了咖啡和这些，我们来看看她提到的一些具体

250
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:51,600
phrases that she used when she was talking about her hair because I think her hair is
短语，关于她的头发，因为我觉得她的头发

251
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,600
very complicated.
很复杂。

252
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,880
It is very complicated.
确实很复杂。

253
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:56,400
Sometimes she washes her hair.
有时候她洗头发。

254
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,200
Sometimes she doesn't wash her hair.
有时候她不洗头发。

255
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,600
Sometimes she blow dries it straight.
有时候她用吹风机吹直。

256
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:05,280
Okay, so to blow dry means that you use a blow dryer.
好的，所以“blow dry”意思是你用吹风机。

257
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,280
That's right.
没错。

258
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:11,640
This is a machine that uses electricity to blow hot air on your hair so that your hair
这是一种用电吹热风到头发上的机器，这样你的头发

259
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:13,480
will dry quickly.
会干得快。

260
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:16,440
But you can blow dry your hair in many ways.
但你可以用很多方式吹干头发。

261
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:20,840
Some people have curly hair and they have special tools for making their hair curly.
有些人有卷发，他们有专门的工具来让头发卷曲。

262
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,520
But she says she blow dries it straight.
但她说她用吹风机吹直。

263
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,920
That means she makes it straight with hot air.
意思是她用热风把头发弄直。

264
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:26,920
Right.
对。

265
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:31,800
So I think the way you do this is you take the blow dryer and a brush and you brush while
所以我觉得做法是，你拿着吹风机和梳子，一边吹

266
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:32,800
you blow dry, right?
一边梳，对吧？

267
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:33,800
Yep.
嗯。

268
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:34,800
Awesome.
太棒了。

269
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:35,800
Making lines.
分线。

270
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,960
See, I know a little bit about this even though I don't have long enough hair for this.
看，我虽然头发不够长，但我也懂一点。

271
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:38,960
No, I guess.
不，我想是吧。

272
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:43,680
Well, maybe you are secretly one of those guys who has a routine like this woman.
嗯，也许你私下里就是那种像这个女人一样有固定流程的人。

273
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:49,920
I don't think I can take this much time in the shower and brushing my hair.
我觉得我花不了这么多时间在淋浴和梳头上。

274
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:55,480
But moving on, actually, I also know this next phrase, to flat iron your hair.
但继续，实际上，我也知道下一个短语，“用直发夹板拉直头发”。

275
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:58,880
Okay, so flat iron is a noun and a verb.
好的，所以“flat iron”既是名词也是动词。

276
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:03,320
So I use a flat iron or I can flat iron my hair.
所以我会用直发夹板，或者我可以拉直头发。

277
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:06,840
This is a tool that we use that's very, very hot.
这是一种我们用的工具，非常非常热。

278
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,840
Think of an iron.
想象一下熨斗。

279
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:14,640
It's very, very hot and it basically presses my hair and makes it very, very, very thin
它非常非常热，基本上压住我的头发，让它变得非常非常薄

280
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:17,320
and flat and straight.
又平又直。

281
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:21,520
So I think people that have straight hair don't need to really flat iron their hair.
所以我觉得有直发的人不需要真的用直发夹板。

282
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:24,920
Nah, but if you have very curly hair, then you need it.
不，但如果你有很卷的头发，那你需要它。

283
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:26,180
So what's the difference?
那有什么区别呢？

284
00:12:26,180 --> 00:12:27,180
Give us the insight here.
给我们讲讲内幕。

285
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:29,800
Why wouldn't you just blow dry it straight?
为什么你不直接用吹风机吹直？

286
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,200
Why do you need to flat iron it?
为什么需要用直发夹板？

287
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:35,200
Because a flat iron makes it more flat.
因为直发夹板能让头发更直。

288
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:41,280
It makes your hair stick together more and it's much, much, much hotter than a blow dryer.
它让头发更贴合，而且比吹风机热得多得多。

289
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:45,660
So I guess if you use a blow dryer, then you have puffy hair or like the next word that
所以我想如果你用吹风机，头发会蓬松，或者像她描述的

290
00:12:45,660 --> 00:12:47,760
she described, frizzy hair.
下一个词，“毛躁的头发”。

291
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:52,920
Okay, so the adjective to describe this kind of hair is frizzy.
好的，所以描述这种头发的形容词是“frizzy”。

292
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:56,680
For example, when it's very rainy, my hair is frizzy.
比如，下雨天的时候，我的头发很毛躁。

293
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:58,080
That means that it sticks out.
意思是它翘起来。

294
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:02,120
It's very thick and not straight.
很厚，不直。

295
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:05,200
It's not curly, but it's messy.
不是卷的，而是乱糟糟的。

296
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,200
It kind of inflates.
有点像膨胀了。

297
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,200
That's right.
没错。

298
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,480
It's like a little balloon.
像个小气球。

299
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:12,560
But the verb here is to frizz.
但这里的动词是“to frizz”。

300
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:15,320
So my hair is frizzing.
所以我的头发在毛躁。

301
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:18,640
And that means that it's getting like this, bigger or inflated.
意思是它变得像这样，更大或膨胀了。

302
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,640
That's right.
没错。

303
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:25,240
So girls who have this problem have it worse during very humid or rainy days.
所以有这问题的女生在潮湿或下雨天更严重。

304
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,960
Not so bad when it's dry.
干燥的时候没那么糟。

305
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:30,920
Okay, so I actually have a little bit of frizzy hair.
好的，其实我头发有点毛躁。

306
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:36,040
That's why I have to use some sort of hair gel or mousse.
所以我得用一些发胶或摩丝。

307
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,880
See, it's not because I'm vain.
看，这不是因为我自恋。

308
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:41,240
It's just because if I don't use this, I'll come in looking like a lion.
只是如果我不用的，我会看起来像头狮子。

309
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:45,240
I think I might have to insist that that happens sometime soon.
我想我得坚持让你尽快那样做一次。

310
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:48,120
We can take a picture and put it on our website, EnglishBot.com.
我们可以拍张照片放到我们网站EnglishBot.com上。

311
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,120
For sure.
当然。

312
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:56,120
All right, so why don't we go back and listen to the dialogue one last time.
好的，那我们不如回去再听一遍对话吧。

313
00:13:56,120 --> 00:14:03,560
Stephanie, did you just get to school?
Stephanie，你刚到学校吗？

314
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:06,360
But you were up and about when I left the dorm this morning.
但我早上离开宿舍的时候你已经起床活动了。

315
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:08,080
That was about an hour and a half ago.
那大约是一个半小时前。

316
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,080
This happens all the time.
这总是发生。

317
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:12,040
Why do you always take so long to get ready in the mornings?
为什么你早上总是花这么长时间准备？

318
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:13,200
It's a skill.
这是一种技能。

319
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,880
What can I say?
我能说什么呢？

320
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:15,920
I don't know why.
我不知道为什么。

321
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,880
I just have a long routine.
我早上的流程很长。

322
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:20,400
Please explain because it makes no sense to me.
请解释一下，因为我不明白。

323
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:23,080
How can a girl's routine be so complicated?
一个女生的流程怎么会这么复杂？

324
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:28,440
You get up, you shower, you get dressed, you brush your teeth, you're out the door.
你起床、洗澡、穿衣服、刷牙，然后出门。

325
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:30,000
Half an hour tops.
最多半小时。

326
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:34,960
Jacob, you have the luxury of having a haircut that rarely needs styling.
雅各布，你幸运的是发型几乎不需要打理。

327
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,080
I don't.
我可不行。

328
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:40,400
I have to set aside about an hour and a half to get ready in the mornings.
我早上得留出一个半小时来准备。

329
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:43,440
Every day, I wake up and head straight for the shower.
每天，我醒来就直接去洗澡。

330
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:45,340
Every second day, I wash my hair.
每隔一天，我会洗一次头发。

331
00:14:45,340 --> 00:14:51,000
If it's a hair washing day, I frequently need to wash my hair twice because it gets really
如果是洗头日，我经常需要洗两次，因为头发会变得很

332
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,000
oily.
油。

333
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,660
Then, I usually put in a conditioner and have to rinse that out too.
然后，我通常会涂护发素，还得把它冲洗干净。

334
00:14:55,660 --> 00:15:01,320
Because my hair is so long, I seldom manage to take a shower in under 20 minutes.
因为我的头发很长，我很少能在20分钟内洗完澡。

335
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:06,080
Afterwards, I often put on a pot of coffee and get dressed while I wait for it to brew.
之后，我经常煮一壶咖啡，在等咖啡煮好的时候穿衣服。

336
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:09,080
I take a long time to get dressed in the morning.
我早上穿衣服要花很长时间。

337
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:12,920
Every now and then, I remember to choose my outfit the night before, but usually, I do
偶尔，我会记得前一天晚上选好衣服，但通常，我都是

338
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,600
it in the morning.
早上才选。

339
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:19,120
In all, getting dressed takes about half an hour, at which time my hair is now semi-dry,
总的来说，穿衣服大约需要半小时，这时我的头发半干了，

340
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:21,200
